  <prompt>Create NEW integration test class `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.Integration/Cache/MetricsDistributedCacheRegistrationTests.cs`. After the full DI graph builds (via the existing WAF fixture pattern), assert: (a) `IDistributedCache` resolves to `MetricsDistributedCache` wrapping the expected inner type (`RedisCache` when Redis enabled, `MemoryDistributedCache` when in dev-fallback); (b) exactly ONE `Meter("Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache")` instance exists at runtime, verified via `MeterListener` enumeration. Test runs as part of `dotnet test`.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with xUnit + WebApplicationFactory + OTel Metrics experience. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor (TEST-MODIFYING override).</role>
  <goal>New test class passes both branches; runs in CI as part of `dotnet test`. Net new tests: 2 (one for decorator resolution, one for Meter count assertion).</goal>
